{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778123095,"nonce":"IDSMPK0CKbGBPQHeiLkIrjd7sMM=","title":"Tighten gitignore whitelist: prevent depth-blind config.json matching for future bulk-artifact trees","message":"Phase 1's gitignore (`58415d2`, merged via `79ee4420`) whitelists `**/config.json` under `results/**` to keep 25 legacy `centerout_*/config.json` and `models/\u003crun\u003e/config.json` stubs trackable. The whitelist is **depth-blind**: any \\`config.json\\` at any depth under \\`results/\\` is trackable, including future bulk-artifact trees like \\`results/\u003cexp\u003e/runpod/\u003crun\u003e/config.json\\`, \\`results/\u003cexp\u003e/modal/\u003crun\u003e/config.json\\`, etc.\n\nThe runpod-specific case bit us at the Phase 2 auth-merge (`75456fec` failed; resolved by moving \\`results/part2_5/runpod/\\` → \\`_artifacts/part2_5/runpod/\\`). But the latent issue persists for future trees.\n\n## Fix\n\nReplace the broad `!results/**/config.json` with depth-/path-specific patterns matching only legitimate spec locations:\n- `!results/*/config.json` (top-level experiment configs)\n- `!results/*/models/*/config.json` (legacy `models/\u003crun\u003e/` structure)\n\nThe new \\`runs/\u003cgroup\u003e__\u003cvariant\u003e/run.json\\` convention is already covered by a separate \\`!results/**/run.json\\` rule, so dropping the broad \\`config.json\\` whitelist doesn't hurt new-style runs.\n\n## Tests\n\nExtend `tests/test_paths.py` with regressions verifying:\n- All existing tracked \\`config.json\\` files (25 of them) remain trackable.\n- Hypothetical future paths like \\`results/\u003cexp\u003e/modal/\u003crun\u003e/config.json\\` and \\`results/\u003cexp\u003e/coreweave/\u003crun\u003e/config.json\\` are ignored.\n- The runpod-style depth-4 pattern is ignored.\n\nCross-refs: \\`58415d2\\` (Phase 1, merged), \\`fd64bb4\\` (Phase 2, merged).","files":null}]}